Today I created html and css file for todo list website. I took some help from a youtube video but the javascript file is not ready yet
#day20 #60DaysOfJs #learningwithkucc

html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>To Do List</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="./style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="box">
        <h1>To Do List</h1>
        <div class="input-box">
            <input class="todo-input" placeholder="Add new task...">
            <button class="add-button">
                <i class="fa fa-plus-circle"></i>
            </button>
        </div>
        <div class="todo-box">
            <ul class="todos"></ul>
            <img class="empty-image" src="./download.jpg">
        </div>
    </div>
    <script src="./script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>


